==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[brýne]]

===Pronunciation===
*brīn, /braɪn/, /<tt>braIn</tt>/

===Noun===
'''brine''' (''uncountable'')

#([[uncountable]])
# Salt [[water]]
water saturated or strongly impregnated with salt; a salt and water solution for pickling; the sea or ocean; the water of the sea; Chem.any saline solution.
:"The ship sank to the briney deep"
:"Do you want the can of tuna in oil or in brine?"

